1
00:00:10,533 --> 00:00:12,500
<i>Grandmohther, you left the rice
on the stove.</i>

2
00:00:12,633 --> 00:00:13,767
<i> It's burnt.</i>

3
00:00:13,900 --> 00:00:16,300
<i>Even the water,
you left the faucet running.</i>

4
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:17,800
<i> I was cooking?</i>

5
00:00:17,933 --> 00:00:18,967
<i> Are you okay?</i>

6
00:00:19,100 --> 00:00:21,667
<i>Sir, someone from Village Amador
called me.</i>

7
00:00:21,800 --> 00:00:24,400
<i>They said they noticed a tenant
who always wears a mask.</i>

8
00:00:24,533 --> 00:00:27,567
<i>Anybody home? Sir,
I'm just conducting a survey.</i>

9
00:00:27,700 --> 00:00:28,567
<i> Mateo Ramos...</i>

10
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:30,400
<i>- Stop! Hey!
- Tonyo!</i>

11
00:00:30,533 --> 00:00:31,600
<i> Move!</i>

12
00:00:34,733 --> 00:00:36,300
<i>That's enough!
You can't escape anymore!</i>

13
00:00:36,433 --> 00:00:37,367
<i> Father, I'm sorry.</i>

14
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:39,333
<i>I'll do everything you command,
Father.</i>

15
00:00:39,467 --> 00:00:41,233
<i>Do you want to talk
to your father?</i>

16
00:00:41,367 --> 00:00:42,800
<i>I really want to apologize
to him.</i>

17
00:00:42,933 --> 00:00:44,367
<i> I can feel him.</i>

18
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:48,233
<i>Your father wants you to know
that he is very happy</i>

19
00:00:48,367 --> 00:00:49,700
<i> that you called him father,</i>

20
00:00:49,833 --> 00:00:51,500
<i>and that he is very proud
of you.</i>

21
00:00:51,633 --> 00:00:52,633
<i> Thank you, Alma.</i>

22
00:00:52,767 --> 00:00:53,700
<i> Sergeant Enriquez.</i>

23
00:00:53,833 --> 00:00:55,000
<i>Mayor,
I'm going to the cemetery.</i>

24
00:00:55,133 --> 00:00:56,167
<i> I'm going to visit father.</i>

25
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:57,233
<i> Just come with us.</i>

26
00:00:57,367 --> 00:00:58,567
<i> We're going there too.</i>

27
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:02,267
<i>No! I will not bring cheap
flowers to my husband's grave.</i>

28
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:03,667
<i> Mom! Bobby, I'm sorry.</i>

29
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:05,500
<i> It's okay, Mayor.</i>

30
00:01:05,633 --> 00:01:11,600
Finally, we have caught
the last fugitive we are after

31
00:01:11,767 --> 00:01:14,133
and the ice pick killer
has been solved.

32
00:01:14,267 --> 00:01:18,500
The same goes for the unsolved
case involving Mateo.

33
00:01:18,633 --> 00:01:21,233
Good job, Conde, Samson.

34
00:01:27,033 --> 00:01:28,833
Too bad, Sir.

35
00:01:28,967 --> 00:01:32,000
If only we had known about
Mateo's story sooner.

36
00:01:32,133 --> 00:01:36,467
We could have helped him
since he was also a victim.

37
00:01:36,600 --> 00:01:38,500
I wish we could have at least
had a chance

38
00:01:38,633 --> 00:01:40,733
to change his view about gays.

39
00:01:40,900 --> 00:01:43,567
because there are many
LGBT members

40
00:01:43,700 --> 00:01:45,567
who are helping our community.

41
00:01:47,733 --> 00:01:49,267
You're right, Conde.

42
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:53,567
And I'm sure
that Mateo's victims

43
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:55,733
were also victims
of opportunity.

44
00:01:55,867 --> 00:02:00,967
We couldn't have done all
of this without your help,

45
00:02:01,100 --> 00:02:03,633
Torres, De Jesus.

46
00:02:03,767 --> 00:02:07,133
Your verification of the tip
is why we found Mateo,

47
00:02:07,267 --> 00:02:08,367
so thank you.

48
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:16,300
And most of all,
I want to thank...

49
00:02:18,933 --> 00:02:21,300
Don't mention it, Tonyo.

50
00:02:21,433 --> 00:02:24,367
I am grateful,
but this is about you.

51
00:02:24,500 --> 00:02:25,733
This is not about me.

52
00:02:25,867 --> 00:02:27,733
So thank you, thank you.

53
00:02:27,867 --> 00:02:29,267
You, Bok?

54
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:30,867
Why? What did you do?

55
00:02:32,133 --> 00:02:36,600
I know I'm the one
who inspires all of you

56
00:02:36,733 --> 00:02:40,133
to do better in your jobs,
right?

57
00:02:40,267 --> 00:02:41,333
Bok...

58
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:43,500
it's not you.

59
00:02:47,267 --> 00:02:51,900
Most of all, I want to thank
Sergeant Bobby Enriquez

60
00:02:52,033 --> 00:02:53,900
because she put all this
together.

61
00:02:54,033 --> 00:02:57,233
Her research and excellent
profiling of the suspects

62
00:02:57,367 --> 00:03:00,467
were the keys in solving
this case.

63
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:02,233
I agree.

64
00:03:02,367 --> 00:03:07,467
Enriquez proved that a good
police officer can solve

65
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:11,433
and help even if she's just
doing a desk job.

66
00:03:11,567 --> 00:03:14,333
Thank you very much
for your cooperation.

67
00:03:14,467 --> 00:03:16,167
Okay, back to work!

68
00:03:19,933 --> 00:03:21,600
Bok, congratulations.

69
00:03:21,767 --> 00:03:22,867
Thank you.

70
00:03:24,100 --> 00:03:25,167
Sir,

71
00:03:26,467 --> 00:03:28,500
where is Sergeant Enriquez,
by the way?

72
00:03:28,633 --> 00:03:32,000
I asked her to take a leave
so she can think things over.

73
00:03:32,867 --> 00:03:35,433
But don't worry,
when she comes back,

74
00:03:35,567 --> 00:03:38,133
I'll personally commend her.

75
00:03:38,267 --> 00:03:39,233
Thank you, Sir.

76
00:04:17,467 --> 00:04:19,700
How should I do it?

77
00:04:19,833 --> 00:04:21,367
Hello, Bobby!

78
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:23,900
We caught Mateo Ramos...

79
00:04:24,933 --> 00:04:26,667
That's too happy. Wait...

80
00:04:28,933 --> 00:04:29,867
Hello, Bobby?

81
00:04:31,100 --> 00:04:32,800
We caught Mateo Ramos.

82
00:04:34,133 --> 00:04:35,767
I think that's too serious.

83
00:04:37,300 --> 00:04:38,767
Oh, whatever.

84
00:04:43,467 --> 00:04:44,533
Miss Jenny...

85
00:04:44,667 --> 00:04:46,200
Where is grandmohther?

86
00:04:46,333 --> 00:04:49,567
Captain? She left a while ago.

87
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:50,700
Is that so?

88
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:53,133
- Okay, thank you.
- Okay.

89
00:05:02,167 --> 00:05:03,067
Hello.

90
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:04,367
Hello?

91
00:05:04,500 --> 00:05:05,500
Bobby...

92
00:05:08,133 --> 00:05:11,833
We already caught Mateo Ramos.

93
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:16,733
Yes, I know.
Noble told me.

94
00:05:20,667 --> 00:05:21,667
Okay.

95
00:05:24,300 --> 00:05:26,567
What, is there anything else
you want to say?

96
00:05:28,533 --> 00:05:29,600
Bobby...

97
00:05:31,433 --> 00:05:32,733
Can we talk?

98
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:35,233
What are we doing?

99
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:40,300
Your tone is still angry.

100
00:05:42,633 --> 00:05:44,300
Are you mad?

101
00:05:44,433 --> 00:05:45,467
What do you think?

102
00:05:46,933 --> 00:05:47,933
Bobby...

103
00:05:49,667 --> 00:05:51,167
just tell me straight.

104
00:05:52,767 --> 00:05:55,333
I'm not a fortune teller
like Alma.

105
00:05:57,367 --> 00:05:58,933
Yes, I'm angry with you!

106
00:05:59,067 --> 00:05:59,833
Happy?

107
00:06:01,567 --> 00:06:03,167
Why would I be happy

108
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:04,867
when you're angry with me?

109
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,800
I don't know about you, Tonyo.

110
00:06:08,067 --> 00:06:08,933
Bobby...

111
00:06:10,633 --> 00:06:12,767
what did I do wrong to you?

112
00:06:14,533 --> 00:06:16,933
You're the only one
who thinks I betrayed you.

113
00:06:17,067 --> 00:06:18,933
Okay, fine,
I'm the bad guy!

114
00:06:19,067 --> 00:06:20,567
Bobby?

115
00:06:20,700 --> 00:06:22,000
Hello?

116
00:06:22,133 --> 00:06:23,133
Bobby?

117
00:06:39,033 --> 00:06:40,667
I think I went too far.

118
00:06:42,167 --> 00:06:44,033
Well, it's obvious!

119
00:06:44,167 --> 00:06:46,500
The answer to his questions
is obvious.

120
00:06:46,633 --> 00:06:48,667
When he could just say sorry,
right?

121
00:06:50,333 --> 00:06:51,500
Annoying.

122
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:55,167
Hey, she's pretending
to be angry,

123
00:06:55,300 --> 00:06:57,200
but it's obvious
that she's in love.

124
00:06:57,333 --> 00:06:58,900
It's driving me crazy.

125
00:07:01,333 --> 00:07:02,533
<i> What's that?</i>

126
00:07:02,667 --> 00:07:05,500
<i>- I'm clingy to you.
- This...</i>

127
00:07:05,633 --> 00:07:06,367
<i> What's that?</i>

128
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:08,800
Mar, Abdul...

129
00:07:08,933 --> 00:07:11,300
- I have good news for you.
- Hey, what's that?

130
00:07:11,433 --> 00:07:13,700
The serial killer
was caught earlier.

131
00:07:13,833 --> 00:07:15,033
Really?

132
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:17,033
Thank you very much, Bobby!

133
00:07:17,167 --> 00:07:19,267
- Really?
- Oh my god.

134
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:22,167
Where is grandmohther?

135
00:07:23,633 --> 00:07:25,000
She's lying down.

136
00:07:25,133 --> 00:07:25,867
She's tired.

137
00:07:27,033 --> 00:07:28,867
When she kept giving us orders
earlier,

138
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,167
and now she's the one
who's tired.

139
00:07:30,300 --> 00:07:31,333
Wait...

140
00:07:31,467 --> 00:07:33,600
Who caught the serial killer?

141
00:07:33,733 --> 00:07:38,033
Well, it's Lieutenant Conde
and his new partner,

142
00:07:38,167 --> 00:07:40,533
Lieutenant Charlie Samson.

143
00:07:42,267 --> 00:07:45,000
Sir Tonyo has a new partner?

144
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:50,833
Charlie, my mortal rival
at the academy.

145
00:07:51,933 --> 00:07:53,400
Academy...

146
00:07:53,533 --> 00:07:54,600
Wait...

147
00:07:54,733 --> 00:07:57,667
If you two entered
the academy together,

148
00:07:57,800 --> 00:08:00,567
why is she a Lieutenant,
and you, just a sergeant?

149
00:08:00,700 --> 00:08:03,000
That's because she's smart-aleck
and a sycophant.

150
00:08:03,133 --> 00:08:04,700
She thinks she's such a beauty.

151
00:08:04,833 --> 00:08:05,967
So she's not beautiful?

152
00:08:06,100 --> 00:08:08,000
Of course not!

153
00:08:08,133 --> 00:08:11,133
She thinks she's so beautiful,
but she's ugly.

154
00:08:11,267 --> 00:08:14,267
Bobby, you're insulting her!

155
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:18,033
If she's ugly,
why are you affected?

156
00:08:18,167 --> 00:08:20,067
Yes, you seem so jealous.

157
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:21,900
Of course not!

158
00:08:22,067 --> 00:08:25,133
I just don't like her because
she thinks so highly of herself!

159
00:08:25,267 --> 00:08:28,367
Imagine, she just moved
to Station 12,

160
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:30,367
but she feels like
she's the queen of the place.

161
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:32,333
She thinks she's so tall

162
00:08:32,467 --> 00:08:34,333
when she's only three feet tall.

163
00:08:35,833 --> 00:08:38,267
Oh my, I'm going to take a bath!

164
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:39,633
You're so annoying!

165
00:08:39,767 --> 00:08:41,333
You're making a hot headed!

166
00:08:41,467 --> 00:08:43,733
- So angry.
- Did you hear that?

167
00:08:43,867 --> 00:08:46,333
She's three feet tall,
so I'm even taller!

168
00:08:46,467 --> 00:08:47,700
Then she must be really ugly.

169
00:08:47,833 --> 00:08:49,100
Yes, that's right, the ugly!

170
00:08:49,233 --> 00:08:51,233
Because based on Bobby,
she's really ugly.

171
00:08:51,367 --> 00:08:54,500
That's right, and so small.
Yuck, disgusting!

172
00:08:54,667 --> 00:08:56,133
- You're even taller.
- Yes!

173
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:58,933
Oh my, grandchild,

174
00:08:59,067 --> 00:09:02,233
thank you for accompanying me
to the market.

175
00:09:02,367 --> 00:09:04,733
Why, Grandmohther?
Don't these two accompany you?

176
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:09,633
Those two, oh my,
they're giving me a headache.

177
00:09:09,767 --> 00:09:13,167
I'm with them,
but they do nothing but gossip.

178
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:14,633
Come on, Grandmohther.

179
00:09:14,767 --> 00:09:17,033
We always go shopping with you.

180
00:09:17,167 --> 00:09:17,967
Yes, that's right!

181
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:20,000
You always make us carry
your purchases.

182
00:09:20,133 --> 00:09:22,100
- There, oh.
- You're with me,

183
00:09:22,233 --> 00:09:23,800
but what's the use?

184
00:09:23,933 --> 00:09:26,800
You're always missing
and gossiping.

185
00:09:26,933 --> 00:09:29,400
- There.
- Captain, I'm sorry.

186
00:09:29,567 --> 00:09:33,067
No, from now on, we'll
prioritize you over gossip.

187
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:35,633
So even if we always go
shopping, that's fine.

188
00:09:35,767 --> 00:09:41,833
Yes, especially since the serial
killer is behind bars, right?

189
00:09:41,967 --> 00:09:45,200
And the beauty queens are safe
and sound again.

190
00:09:45,333 --> 00:09:47,767
Yes, and that's because
of Bobby.

191
00:09:47,900 --> 00:09:49,767
<i>Thanks to Bobby,
and because of you,</i>

192
00:09:49,900 --> 00:09:51,633
<i>the serial killer was caught,
right?</i>

193
00:09:51,767 --> 00:09:54,033
And why are you thanking Bobby?

194
00:09:54,167 --> 00:09:56,667
She wasn't the one
who caught the killer.

195
00:09:56,800 --> 00:09:58,100
Just FYI.

196
00:09:58,233 --> 00:10:00,067
That's Lieutenant Conde and me.

197
00:10:21,367 --> 00:10:22,367
Bobby!

198
00:10:23,533 --> 00:10:24,500
Where?

199
00:10:24,633 --> 00:10:25,567
Bok,

200
00:10:26,633 --> 00:10:28,700
if you had called her,

201
00:10:28,833 --> 00:10:32,667
you wouldn't be wandering around
like a giraffe.

202
00:10:34,633 --> 00:10:36,100
- What are you talking about?
- What are you talking about?

203
00:10:37,900 --> 00:10:40,400
Bok, me, of all people!

204
00:10:40,533 --> 00:10:42,933
Well, I know you well.

205
00:10:43,067 --> 00:10:44,267
Fool!

206
00:10:46,100 --> 00:10:47,900
You know, Bok...

207
00:10:48,033 --> 00:10:53,433
Bobby, Noble said,
is still on vacation.

208
00:10:53,567 --> 00:10:56,133
She's supposed to report
tomorrow.

209
00:10:56,267 --> 00:10:57,300
See?

210
00:10:57,433 --> 00:10:59,267
Even that, I know very well.

211
00:11:03,233 --> 00:11:04,300
Call her.

212
00:11:04,433 --> 00:11:05,567
Bok...

213
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:08,267
we talked last night.

214
00:11:08,433 --> 00:11:10,067
So, are you and Bobby okay?

215
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:10,867
You guys made up?

216
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:12,800
I think she's even angrier.

217
00:11:13,900 --> 00:11:15,033
What did you do?

218
00:11:15,167 --> 00:11:16,300
It's not my fault.

219
00:11:16,433 --> 00:11:17,967
You think I'm guilty?

220
00:11:18,100 --> 00:11:18,933
I told Bobby...

221
00:11:19,067 --> 00:11:21,233
I talked to her.
I said, "Tell me straight,

222
00:11:22,467 --> 00:11:24,300
I'm not a fortune-teller, Bok."

223
00:11:26,067 --> 00:11:27,200
Bok,

224
00:11:28,767 --> 00:11:31,233
you know what's wrong
with you and Bobby?

225
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:34,433
What?

226
00:11:34,567 --> 00:11:36,400
You're both full of pride.

227
00:11:36,533 --> 00:11:38,167
Okay, this.

228
00:11:38,300 --> 00:11:41,767
Since you two fought,
has anyone apologized to you?

229
00:11:41,933 --> 00:11:42,967
Yes, Bok.

230
00:11:43,100 --> 00:11:45,100
I'm always apologizing.

231
00:11:45,233 --> 00:11:46,867
- Really?
- Yes.

232
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:47,967
Oh, okay, okay.

233
00:11:48,100 --> 00:11:49,500
I'll call Bobby now.

234
00:11:49,633 --> 00:11:51,367
I'll make sure
what you're saying is true.

235
00:11:51,500 --> 00:11:54,033
- Don't, hey, hey.
- No, no, that's not possible.

236
00:11:54,167 --> 00:11:55,633
Wait, wait, wait.

237
00:11:55,767 --> 00:11:57,600
Hello?

238
00:11:57,733 --> 00:12:02,133
What's this I heard about Bok
apologizing to you

239
00:12:02,267 --> 00:12:03,833
and you still
haven't forgiven him?

240
00:12:03,967 --> 00:12:05,733
What kind of person are you?

241
00:12:07,933 --> 00:12:09,700
No, no, just kidding.

242
00:12:09,833 --> 00:12:10,467
- I don't have Bobby's number.
- Nothing?

243
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,667
Bok,

244
00:12:14,833 --> 00:12:18,767
my point is,
just understand the person.

245
00:12:18,900 --> 00:12:19,467
She recently lost someone.

246
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:21,300
Her father died.

247
00:12:21,433 --> 00:12:25,700
All Bobby is looking for from
you is extra understanding.

248
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:26,767
Okay?

249
00:12:27,867 --> 00:12:29,867
Stop competing with her.

250
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:32,300
You also have a hard time
when she's angry.

251
00:12:35,300 --> 00:12:38,567
You know, it's my fault.

252
00:12:40,733 --> 00:12:44,400
Because I haven't taught you
how to do this yet.

253
00:12:45,767 --> 00:12:48,567
This is a whole different level
when it comes to relationships.

254
00:12:48,733 --> 00:12:50,767
Next time, I'll teach you.

255
00:12:57,633 --> 00:12:59,033
Who are you?

256
00:12:59,167 --> 00:13:00,767
Lieutenant Charlie Samson.

257
00:13:00,900 --> 00:13:02,133
Bobby!

258
00:13:02,267 --> 00:13:04,733
She's the cop with an attitude
that you were talking about!

259
00:13:04,867 --> 00:13:07,633
You were insulting her.
Aren't you?

260
00:13:07,767 --> 00:13:15,033
You're the ugly, not-so-good,
not-so-tall,

261
00:13:15,167 --> 00:13:18,333
who wants to rule Station 12.

262
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:21,867
Bobby, you're right.

263
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:28,100
She's not that beautiful,
she's ugly.

264
00:13:30,367 --> 00:13:31,533
Hey...

265
00:13:31,667 --> 00:13:34,667
A gay man with a beard

266
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:37,733
and a gay man
who hasn't grown much.

267
00:13:38,667 --> 00:13:39,667
Hi.

268
00:13:40,933 --> 00:13:42,300
Do you need anything from me?

269
00:13:43,433 --> 00:13:45,867
Mar, Abdul, go inside.

270
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:46,900
Take grandmother with you.

271
00:13:47,033 --> 00:13:48,700
Yes, Cap, let's go.

272
00:13:48,833 --> 00:13:49,933
We can't handle her.

273
00:13:55,233 --> 00:13:57,633
- Your mom, blue!
- Grandmother!

274
00:13:58,800 --> 00:13:59,667
Come on.

275
00:14:03,267 --> 00:14:04,667
What are you doing here?

276
00:14:04,800 --> 00:14:07,300
Is Station 12 so boring,

277
00:14:07,433 --> 00:14:09,533
that you went out of your way
to visit who you envied?

278
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:13,300
Me, jealous of you?

279
00:14:14,367 --> 00:14:17,833
Well, Tonyo and I just finished
our successful partnership.

280
00:14:17,967 --> 00:14:19,600
Case closed immediately.

281
00:14:19,733 --> 00:14:24,433
And you, how long did it take
you to close Amo's case?

282
00:14:24,567 --> 00:14:26,567
Okay, fine,
you're the good one.

283
00:14:26,700 --> 00:14:27,567
Come on.

284
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:28,933
Bobby...

285
00:14:29,100 --> 00:14:31,500
I came here out of respect
for you.

286
00:14:31,633 --> 00:14:32,833
Respect?

287
00:14:32,967 --> 00:14:35,300
I'm going to ask
for your permission.

288
00:14:35,433 --> 00:14:38,067
Maybe you can set me up
with Tonyo.

289
00:14:39,700 --> 00:14:41,100
You guys didn't become
a couple, right?

290
00:14:43,833 --> 00:14:46,133
Yes, we're not together.

291
00:14:46,267 --> 00:14:47,300
Good!

292
00:14:47,433 --> 00:14:49,933
I knew it,
Tonyo wouldn't like you.

293
00:14:51,467 --> 00:14:52,433
So can you?

294
00:14:54,100 --> 00:14:55,800
Do you like Tonyo?

295
00:14:55,933 --> 00:14:58,233
Okay, it's up to you.

296
00:14:58,367 --> 00:15:00,267
If you want, even the whole
Station 12,

297
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:01,400
go ahead and do it.

298
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:03,233
If you want, even the Chief,
you can have him.

299
00:15:04,767 --> 00:15:06,233
Just some advice, Charlie,

300
00:15:07,567 --> 00:15:09,633
don't be too obsessed with me,
okay?

301
00:15:10,767 --> 00:15:13,100
Because I might think
I'm your type.

302
00:15:14,700 --> 00:15:15,733
Okay.

303
00:15:23,633 --> 00:15:24,700
Boss,

304
00:15:24,833 --> 00:15:26,900
the person who has collected
your million-peso reward

305
00:15:27,033 --> 00:15:28,900
for the serial killer is lucky.

306
00:15:29,033 --> 00:15:30,467
A small price to pay

307
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:34,333
to stop talking
about those ghost projects.

308
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:38,033
Are you sure that the engineer
won't betray us?

309
00:15:38,167 --> 00:15:39,700
No, Boss.

310
00:15:39,833 --> 00:15:44,833
Every member of his family
is guarded by our people.

311
00:15:44,967 --> 00:15:46,567
He won't tell.

312
00:15:46,700 --> 00:15:47,667
That's good.

313
00:15:49,033 --> 00:15:51,867
I don't want what happened
to Monty to happen again.

314
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:53,833
He'll take us to hell
with him.

315
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:56,267
I'm not ready yet.

316
00:15:57,300 --> 00:16:00,467
Boss, shouldn't we look
for a replacement

317
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:01,933
for Monty at the university?

318
00:16:02,067 --> 00:16:05,233
Well, we've already lost a lot
when the drug trade stopped

319
00:16:05,367 --> 00:16:07,033
at the university.

320
00:16:07,167 --> 00:16:10,467
The police are keeping
a close eye on the university.

321
00:16:11,533 --> 00:16:13,000
And one more thing,

322
00:16:13,133 --> 00:16:15,633
I don't want my sister
to get involved again.

323
00:16:29,233 --> 00:16:31,567
Vince, what?

324
00:16:31,700 --> 00:16:34,600
We've been here a while,
but you're not talking to me.

325
00:16:36,933 --> 00:16:39,833
It's still like a dream
to be with you.

326
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:46,333
Why did you slap me?

327
00:16:46,467 --> 00:16:49,267
So that you'd realize
that this isn't a dream.

328
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:51,300
We're here together.

329
00:16:51,433 --> 00:16:52,967
I don't know.

330
00:16:54,300 --> 00:16:56,133
But you know, Vince,

331
00:16:56,267 --> 00:16:59,067
I sense that you want
to say something.

332
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:01,333
What is it?
Tell me.

333
00:17:02,900 --> 00:17:06,300
Okay, if you don't tell me,
I'm going home.

334
00:17:09,767 --> 00:17:11,567
Hey, Faye,
wait a minute.

335
00:17:14,767 --> 00:17:18,233
I still can't get your brother
out of my head.

336
00:17:19,900 --> 00:17:22,100
It's like he doesn't want me
for you.

337
00:17:22,233 --> 00:17:24,767
Vince, is that all?

338
00:17:24,900 --> 00:17:30,067
Didn't I tell you that I think
my brother likes you?

339
00:17:31,367 --> 00:17:36,400
But if you're still bothered,
then prove it to him.

340
00:17:36,533 --> 00:17:39,333
Prove it to everyone
that you deserve me.

341
00:17:41,467 --> 00:17:42,700
And ever since,

342
00:17:42,833 --> 00:17:45,467
my brother hasn't interfered
in my love life,

343
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:48,300
so you have nothing
to worry about.

344
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:57,800
We need to change our system now
that I'm the Mayor.

345
00:17:57,933 --> 00:17:59,500
It's hard if they see
a loophole in me,

346
00:17:59,633 --> 00:18:01,700
and I'll be out of office soon.

347
00:18:01,833 --> 00:18:06,167
Continue selling drugs,
but not here.

348
00:18:06,300 --> 00:18:09,000
Find another place first.

349
00:18:09,133 --> 00:18:12,533
I want to keep Calabari
clean for now

350
00:18:14,300 --> 00:18:16,467
as long as people love me.

351
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:22,867
And when they think
I'm their salvation,

352
00:18:23,033 --> 00:18:24,767
we'll have them by the neck.

353
00:18:26,333 --> 00:18:30,967
And when they believe,
we can do whatever we want.

354
00:18:31,100 --> 00:18:33,133
So be doubly careful.

355
00:18:33,267 --> 00:18:36,500
You, Roman, you still have
a bounty on your head,

356
00:18:36,633 --> 00:18:38,467
just keep hiding.

357
00:18:38,600 --> 00:18:40,800
No problem, for you, Mayor.

358
00:18:41,900 --> 00:18:45,033
Boss, I'll take care
of Roman's territory first.

359
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:48,667
Dante, just make sure you
won't be compromised, okay?

360
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:51,267
The police are looking for you,
too, Robles said.

361
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:52,800
Remember this.

362
00:18:52,933 --> 00:18:56,467
If the police catch you
and you point me out,

363
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:01,233
I'll wipe out your race.

364
00:19:09,333 --> 00:19:12,367
Have you done any research
on this guy?

365
00:19:12,500 --> 00:19:14,733
Sir, we don't know
his real name yet

366
00:19:14,867 --> 00:19:16,767
because he used an alias here
at the Station

367
00:19:16,900 --> 00:19:18,067
and in Calabari State.

368
00:19:18,200 --> 00:19:21,267
All we know is that
he's bconnected to Mandong Warak

369
00:19:21,400 --> 00:19:23,033
and the pusher, Monty.

370
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:27,900
Bok, this is a big case
if we close it.

371
00:19:28,033 --> 00:19:29,733
It's as big as Boss Amo's.

372
00:19:31,733 --> 00:19:34,667
Have you talked to him
about this?

373
00:19:34,800 --> 00:19:38,067
Maybe he's just one of his men.

374
00:19:39,233 --> 00:19:41,300
Well, that's the thing.

375
00:19:41,433 --> 00:19:47,067
Your father said, since we don't
believe he's innocent,

376
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:48,733
he doesn't want to cooperate.

377
00:19:51,233 --> 00:19:52,633
If he doesn't want to,
then don't!

378
00:19:55,833 --> 00:20:00,100
This guy probably used something
to get here to the station

379
00:20:00,233 --> 00:20:01,933
and also to the Calabari State
University.

380
00:20:03,400 --> 00:20:06,600
Have you checked the CCTV
footages around the area?

381
00:20:06,733 --> 00:20:09,833
Yes, Bok, but it's really
negative.

382
00:20:09,967 --> 00:20:12,233
What you said in the report

383
00:20:12,367 --> 00:20:14,800
is that he handed over money
to Mando, right?

384
00:20:14,933 --> 00:20:15,967
Yes, Sir.

385
00:20:16,100 --> 00:20:19,933
Our theory is that the money
was stuffed into bread.

386
00:20:20,067 --> 00:20:22,033
The CCTV footage captured

387
00:20:22,167 --> 00:20:25,533
that the guy gave
Mandong Warak a bread.

388
00:20:25,667 --> 00:20:29,067
Did this guy hand over money
in a bread to Mando?

389
00:20:30,867 --> 00:20:32,200
Better yet,

390
00:20:32,333 --> 00:20:36,033
go around the ATM around
Calabari State Prison.

391
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:37,933
It's possible
that he withdrew the money

392
00:20:38,067 --> 00:20:39,767
that he was going to give
to Mando.

393
00:20:39,900 --> 00:20:44,133
Also find out from which bakery
those breads were bought.

394
00:20:44,267 --> 00:20:45,567
- Copy, Bok.
- Yes, Sir.

395
00:20:47,267 --> 00:20:48,467
Bok, you know,

396
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:53,033
I'm happy while watching you
because I see myself in you.

397
00:20:53,167 --> 00:20:55,633
We have the same approach,
the same way of thinking.

398
00:20:55,767 --> 00:20:58,267
That's why we're perfect
partners.

399
00:20:58,400 --> 00:21:00,400
Tonyo and I
are more compatible.

400
00:21:04,367 --> 00:21:05,033
As partners.

401
00:21:06,333 --> 00:21:09,233
1-4-1 100 percent batting
average.

402
00:21:11,367 --> 00:21:12,967
Lieutenant Conde,

403
00:21:13,100 --> 00:21:15,633
you're really in demand
at Station 12, aren't you?

404
00:21:15,767 --> 00:21:19,433
Don't you have another partner,
Sergeant Enriquez?

405
00:21:19,567 --> 00:21:21,333
Sergeant Enriquez!

406
00:21:21,467 --> 00:21:23,700
We all don't stand a chance
against her,

407
00:21:23,833 --> 00:21:25,867
not even you,
Lieutenant Samson.

408
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:30,400
That's Tonyo's favorite partner.

409
00:21:30,533 --> 00:21:31,500
- Hey.
- Isn't that right, Bok?

410
00:21:31,633 --> 00:21:32,733
You're full of foolishness.

411
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:37,567
Tonyo, Paloma and I
are going out later.

412
00:21:37,700 --> 00:21:39,567
We're having a few drinks
after duty.

413
00:21:39,700 --> 00:21:41,367
Maybe you want to come along?

414
00:21:49,367 --> 00:21:51,333
What's the update on you
and Tonyo, Bobby?

415
00:21:51,467 --> 00:21:53,833
Yes, of course. I haven't seen
Sir Tonyo either.

416
00:21:55,300 --> 00:21:58,367
He called earlier
but I failed to answer.

417
00:21:58,500 --> 00:22:00,467
Well, he didn't message me
afterwards.

418
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:01,767
Maybe he just accidentally
dialed it.

419
00:22:03,267 --> 00:22:07,967
Or he didn't text you
because he didn't like texting.

420
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:11,233
Well, he probably wanted
to hear your voice.

421
00:22:11,367 --> 00:22:12,767
Right?

422
00:22:12,900 --> 00:22:15,400
And Bobby didn't answer

423
00:22:15,567 --> 00:22:19,133
because he wanted Tonyo
to come over here.

424
00:22:21,233 --> 00:22:23,733
- What's with you?
- Stop it.

425
00:22:23,867 --> 00:22:28,100
Hey, Alicia,
stop seeing that guy!

426
00:22:28,233 --> 00:22:30,833
You're not going to get anything
out of that Joaquin!

427
00:22:32,700 --> 00:22:34,333
Who's Alicia?

428
00:22:34,467 --> 00:22:36,367
Bobby, is that your middle name?
Bobby Alicia?

429
00:22:36,500 --> 00:22:38,633
Oh, no,
that's my mother's name.

430
00:22:40,033 --> 00:22:43,767
Grandmother,
why did you call me Alicia?

431
00:22:43,900 --> 00:22:45,100
This is Bobby.

432
00:22:45,233 --> 00:22:46,233
I know.

433
00:22:47,300 --> 00:22:49,767
Why would I call you Alicia

434
00:22:49,933 --> 00:22:53,000
when I know you're Bobby,
my grandchild?

435
00:22:53,133 --> 00:22:57,133
Captain, you called Bobby
by another name.

436
00:22:58,433 --> 00:22:59,600
Yes, Captain.

437
00:22:59,733 --> 00:23:01,567
You even told her

438
00:23:01,700 --> 00:23:04,600
"Hey, Alicia.
Stop seeing that guy.

439
00:23:04,733 --> 00:23:05,667
Stop seeing Joaquin.

440
00:23:05,800 --> 00:23:07,333
You won't get anything
out of it."

441
00:23:07,467 --> 00:23:08,433
That's what you said.

442
00:23:08,567 --> 00:23:10,433
Hey you two,
stop picking on me.

443
00:23:10,567 --> 00:23:12,567
I know you're playing
a prank on me.

444
00:23:13,633 --> 00:23:15,933
I'll just go to the room
and eat.

445
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:20,967
And why should I call her Alicia
when she's Bobby?

446
00:23:21,100 --> 00:23:22,800
What happened
to your grandmother?

447
00:23:22,967 --> 00:23:24,167
Yes, Bobby.

448
00:23:24,300 --> 00:23:27,900
I've noticed that grandmother
seems to be getting forgetful.

449
00:23:28,033 --> 00:23:30,133
She seems lost now.

450
00:23:30,267 --> 00:23:31,733
Maybe you're stressing her out?

451
00:23:31,867 --> 00:23:32,933
Hey, of course not!

452
00:23:33,067 --> 00:23:34,800
We're good girls, right?

453
00:23:34,933 --> 00:23:40,333
Yes. But, Bobby, what if we take
Captain for a check-up?

454
00:23:40,467 --> 00:23:41,600
What do you think?

455
00:23:58,700 --> 00:24:00,800
That's right,
I'll ask you to do something.

456
00:24:00,933 --> 00:24:01,567
What's that, boss?

457
00:24:01,700 --> 00:24:03,933
Ma'am, I'm sorry for my mistake.

458
00:24:04,067 --> 00:24:06,467
I didn't mean to hurt you again.

459
00:24:06,600 --> 00:24:08,900
So, Bobby, let's work this out.

460
00:24:09,033 --> 00:24:11,567
Love, Tonyo.

461
00:24:11,700 --> 00:24:13,700
Do you think that would work
with Bobby?

462
00:24:13,833 --> 00:24:15,233
It worked before, Bok.

463
00:24:15,367 --> 00:24:18,467
What's the reason you came here
to see us?

464
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:21,700
To talk to you about
your grandchild

465
00:24:21,833 --> 00:24:24,900
who's been forcing herself
on our family.

466
00:24:25,033 --> 00:24:28,467
Glen, I saw how you looked
at that young man.

467
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:29,500
Don't do it.

468
00:24:29,667 --> 00:24:30,867
Where is grandmother?

469
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:35,300
Ma'am Sophia threatened Captain
about your inheritance.

470
00:24:35,433 --> 00:24:36,233
What?
